%% Tower of Babel - Order Data Pipeline Sequence Diagram
%% Shows the temporal flow of messages through the system

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant OrderService as Order Service<br/>(Java/Kotlin:9080)
    participant Kafka as Kafka Broker<br/>(29092)
    participant SchemaReg as Schema Registry<br/>(8081)
    participant Inventory as Inventory Service<br/>(Python:9000)
    participant Analytics as Analytics API<br/>(Node.js:9300)

    Note over Client,Analytics: ✅ SUCCESSFUL PATH: Avro Serialization with Schema Registry

    Client->>+OrderService: POST /orders/avro<br/>userId, amount, items
    
    OrderService->>OrderService: Create Order object
    OrderService->>OrderService: OrderEvent.newBuilder()<br/>setOrderId, setUserId<br/>setAmount, setStatus
    
    OrderService->>+SchemaReg: Register/Fetch Schema<br/>OrderEvent schema
    SchemaReg-->>-OrderService: Schema ID: 1
    
    OrderService->>OrderService: KafkaAvroSerializer<br/>Add magic byte (0x00)<br/>Add schema ID (1)<br/>Serialize to binary
    
    OrderService->>+Kafka: Publish to 'orders' topic<br/>magic byte + schema_id + binary
    OrderService-->>-Client: 200 OK order created
    
    par Inventory Service Consumes
        Kafka->>+Inventory: Poll message
        Inventory->>Inventory: Check magic byte = 0x00
        Inventory->>Inventory: Extract schema ID from bytes[1:5]
        
        Inventory->>+SchemaReg: GET /schemas/ids/1
        SchemaReg-->>-Inventory: OrderEvent schema JSON
        
        Inventory->>Inventory: avro.schema.parse(schema)
        Inventory->>Inventory: DatumReader.read(decoder)
        Inventory->>Inventory: Extract orderId, userId, amount, status
        Inventory->>Inventory: Store in inventory_store[orderId]
        Inventory-->>-Kafka: Commit offset
        
        Note over Inventory: ✅ Successfully deserialized<br/>No type errors
    and Analytics API Consumes
        Kafka->>+Analytics: Poll message
        Analytics->>Analytics: Check message format
        
        Analytics->>+SchemaReg: AvroDeserializer<br/>Auto-fetch schema
        SchemaReg-->>-Analytics: OrderEvent schema
        
        Analytics->>Analytics: deserializer.deserialize()<br/>Decode Avro binary
        Analytics->>Analytics: Convert to Order model<br/>source = 'avro'
        Analytics->>Analytics: analyticsService.addOrder()
        Analytics->>Analytics: Socket.IO broadcast
        Analytics-->>-Kafka: Commit offset
        
        Note over Analytics: ✅ Successfully deserialized<br/>Type-safe conversion
    end

    Note over Client,Analytics: ⚠️ PROBLEMATIC PATH: JSON Serialization (No Schema)

    Client->>+OrderService: POST /orders<br/>userId, amount, items
    
    OrderService->>OrderService: Create Order object<br/>(camelCase fields)
    OrderService->>OrderService: JsonSerializer<br/>No schema validation
    
    OrderService->>+Kafka: Publish to 'orders' topic<br/>JSON with orderId, userId, etc
    OrderService-->>-Client: 200 OK order created
    
    par Inventory Service Attempts JSON
        Kafka->>+Inventory: Poll message
        Inventory->>Inventory: Check magic byte ≠ 0x00
        Inventory->>Inventory: json.loads(message)
        Inventory->>Inventory: _extract_field(['order_id', 'orderId'])
        Inventory->>Inventory: _extract_field(['user_id', 'userId'])
        
        alt Field names match
            Inventory->>Inventory: Store in inventory_store
            Note over Inventory: ⚠️ Works but fragile<br/>Depends on field name guessing
        else Field names don't match
            Inventory->>Inventory: ValueError: Missing field
            Note over Inventory: ❌ Deserialization failed<br/>Error count++
        end
        Inventory-->>-Kafka: Commit offset
    and Analytics API Attempts JSON
        Kafka->>+Analytics: Poll message
        Analytics->>Analytics: JSON.parse(message)
        Analytics->>Analytics: Type conversions:<br/>BigDecimal → string
        
        alt Type conversion succeeds
            Analytics->>Analytics: analyticsService.addOrder()
            Note over Analytics: ⚠️ Works but type unsafe<br/>Potential data corruption
        else Type conversion fails
            Analytics->>Analytics: NaN or parsing error
            Note over Analytics: ❌ Invalid data stored<br/>Error count++
        end
        Analytics-->>-Kafka: Commit offset
    end

    Note over Client,Analytics: 🔍 Key Differences

    rect rgb(144, 238, 144)
        Note over OrderService,Analytics: Avro Path Benefits:<br/>✅ Schema validation at write time<br/>✅ Schema evolution support<br/>✅ Type safety across languages<br/>✅ Automatic schema distribution<br/>✅ Compact binary format
    end

    rect rgb(255, 182, 193)
        Note over OrderService,Analytics: JSON Path Issues:<br/>❌ No schema enforcement<br/>❌ Field name mismatches<br/>❌ Type conversion errors<br/>❌ Manual field mapping<br/>❌ Larger message size
    end
